  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Validation evidence is drawn from a prospective bench study in which pump-outlet blood samples were collected under five flow-speed operating points and analysed for plasma-free haemoglobin; the study protocol was reviewed by the biocompatibility team and the resulting dataset is cited throughout this assessment as the primary experimental basis for the validation claims.",
