      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Bench haemolysis index comparison — five operating points",
      "description": "Predicted relative haemolysis index (RH) values from the CFD model were compared against plasma-free haemoglobin measurements obtained from the prospective bench data-collection study. Across all five flow-speed combinations the model predictions fell within ±15 % of the measured values, and all RH predictions remained below the acceptance threshold of 1.0. The study team notes that the bench data were gathered under conditions representative of clinical CPB operation, and the close agreement between simulation and measurement provides strong evidence of model validity for the intended COU. The activity is described in detail in the supporting technical report and is considered the principal validation evidence for this assessment.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
