        "name": "Prospective bench haemolysis data-collection study",
        "description": "Blood samples were drawn from the pump outlet at each of five pre-specified flow-speed operating points during routine pump characterisation runs. Plasma-free haemoglobin was quantified via spectrophotometry. Operating conditions (flow rate, rotational speed, temperature, anticoagulation) were recorded but not independently randomised or controlled by the study team; the pump was operated by the device manufacturer's technicians under their standard characterisation protocol. Data were subsequently provided to the modelling team for comparison with CFD predictions.",
        "startedAtTime": "2024-03-10T08:00:00Z",
