      "description": "For Model Risk Level 2 Class II devices, validation of the haemolysis prediction capability shall be supported by a controlled experiment in which operating conditions are independently randomised and regulated by the study team, enabling causal attribution of observed haemolysis levels to specific pump operating parameters. The controlled-experiment requirement ensures that confounding variables are eliminated and that the resulting dataset provides a defensible basis for model validation under ASME V&V 40.",
